research_municipality_step.notes: Granbury, TX operates under a Council-Manager form of government, which is categorized as 'mayor_council' for this response. The Mayor and five Councilpersons are elected at large by place for three-year terms. Jim Jarratt was reelected as Mayor in November 2025. Bruce Wadley (Place 3) and Zebedee 'Zeb' Ullom (Place 5) were elected unopposed in November 2024. Eddie Rodriguez (Place 2), Skip Overdier (Place 4), and Greg Corrigan (Place 6) are listed as incumbents.
